<TITLE> Pranab Mukherjee arrives in Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DHAKA, Dec 1 (bdnews24.com) -- Indian external affairs minister Pranab Mukherjee arrived in Dhaka Saturday morning on a day-long tour of cyclone-hit areas in southern Bangladesh. "I would like to make more announcements today. Given the magnitude of the natural calamity, India has decided to waive the ban on the exports of rice to Bangladesh for an additional five lakh tonnes of rice," he told reporters after he arrived at Zia International Airport at 9:15am. India will propose to Bangladesh its willingness to adopt 10 severely-affected coastal villages for rehabilitation, Mukherjee said. The minister handed over token relief materials to foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury at the airport. bdn
